INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES (1,1,'Annmarie Skinner','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100751983058143570475/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJokXmoIc1aZIw61teOBf7ng2D5r2kUXGuqp3NHCXySOxDKeQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Went here today with my 4 daughters, ages 15, 18, 20 and 26. We had a fab time. My youngest especially enjoyed it and interacted throughout. Yes it’s a little out the way, but the trams are really easy to navigate to and from the centre, and cheap too! We got an uber there to ensure we wasn’t late, then tram into the city to explore some more. Was a nice couple hours spent siding something different. Staff are super friendly and helpful too.','2025-10-02 20:36:57','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:07'),(2,1,'Jenny Sun','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116859530143438484891/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdYCBwY7fKwmVTQvSsihXXOT4BimrE8V22PI7FNot7pgnA82a3=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Went to Amaze with a friend and it was such a fun experience! We were just goofing around and loved the vibes. The rooms are really cool with lights, sounds, and lasers. It was different than we expected but in a good way. We got tickets on discount which made it even better. It’s probably a one-time fun thing, but definitely worth checking out if you want something unique in Amsterdam!\n\nAlso don’t go if you have epilepsy.','2025-09-05 12:55:33','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:07'),(3,1,'Zea Cuervo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101241552088271842939/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeKyFFIgQjZmMHhUL073Bbf2Vj1oKL3pYoRPNqcCDqfMju2kU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'A must do in Amsterdam. The best place for someone who appreciates art, electronic music and visuals. Every room felt like a different part of a dream.\n\nStaff are really the best and the cocktails are a must try. The neon sour cocktail and the Amaze liquor, super recommended.\n\nThanks to ID&T for creating these kind of spaces.','2025-10-16 16:27:03','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:07'),(4,1,'Andres Hernandez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101047718060416649382/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_-sQLxgeKWy_i05gPgObiT-2vOS19QovbJJkTpNWNbhdmGHnQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'The best place to really understand rave culture. Amazing staff. I would have spent all my day here.\n\nI can’t stress enough how awesome and kind the staff are. Thank you so much guys.','2025-10-16 15:58:19','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:07'),(5,1,'Klara Pehar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117169716056585365240/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDy7Mo63YazKJ1QebO5uwPLHIa-5JUXP57Lj3vi744b2Zi6K0i=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I went with my parents — one of the coolest activities you can do in Amsterdam! 🙌🏻🙌🏻\nIt’s basically an interactive light and laser show, accompanied by amazing sound and music.\nThe experience is set up across several rooms, and you move from one to the next without knowing what to expect. Each space is a surprise — and every one is unique, fun, and super immersive. I won’t go into too much detail so it stays a surprise for you!\nIf you’ve got an hour or an hour and a half of free time, definitely check it out.\nIt’s great for kids, adults, and even older visitors. Just a heads-up: it’s not recommended for people with epilepsy, as the lights and effects could trigger seizures.\n\nWill go again, once I come back in Ams💙','2025-10-21 09:00:27','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:07'),(6,2,'Jun Herrera','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112138508941599176998/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-fdsj1Rv8W0hjFF1_sE6w4nvHe7vaigYN5sHSfP7eJlQwTMsa=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',4,'This cruise will get you around Amsterdam City. The boat captain will give you a glimpse of Amsterdam buildings and histories. It\'s a smooth sailing along the canal and open bay. Great ride.','2025-05-30 23:29:07','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:45'),(7,2,'VENKATESH PRABHU L','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117977748542127053861/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK0lu0aXsgABVDfMj1QBUo_xA7wYEsXp4vUnl_feC0PSpou3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'For any first time visitor to Amsterdam, a cruise on Amsterdam\'s canals is a must. By opting for it early in your trip, you stand to get a broad idea about city and the attractions it holds for you.','2025-08-11 04:52:25','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:45'),(8,2,'Krys K','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110392396542607213431/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwHSEpo_dJc9z9BAeeTTH3LUp5YgJPp5Y-Ll8X4fcnhR-3LY1D9A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Pleasant cruise on the canal with very little wait time. Staff is excellent. The boats are well kept up so you can enjoy the view from the large windows.','2025-01-03 12:29:45','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:45'),(9,2,'KN IWN','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113234314517691749806/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQWVPNtPSSNVBgnaEUzt1ume-k7USnZ0VOVElq2x0L7x2XDHji=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'When you are tired from walking around Amsterdam then why not just take a boat tour. This tour is quite nice as they have so many languages to choose from and we were quite surprised that there is Thai language too.\n\nOur boat has the glass roof which is quite nice when it’s cold outside. The window can be open if you feel too warm. To be honest, I would recommend to go with open air boat if it’s nice weather and not too cold.\n\nThe audio guide will explain you each highlight spot which is quite good + on the table is the map so you know where is it located or at least you know where you are.\n\nAt some point, it could become boring as you just sit inside the boat. Anyway, our boat rider is quite funny and sarcastic which make us don’t feel so sleepy.','2024-10-28 16:36:03','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:45'),(10,2,'Prabu M','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115122743546895562193/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYaMtkh480dZJQ3Sq6N5EZ6J1Tp99C0yTyoTtkGI8UWE7sPTHU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'The canal boat tour in Amsterdam is an absolute must-do, even in winter, thanks to the covered and heated boats. The one-hour ride offers breathtaking views of the city’s iconic canals, charming bridges, and historic architecture. As you glide through the waterways, you’ll also get to listen to fascinating stories about Amsterdam’s history. It’s a relaxing and scenic experience perfect for families and a great way to see the city from a unique perspective.','2024-12-23 20:32:16','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:45'),(11,3,'Jatin Khodiar','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108190729923183217438/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5Q5poJGI7hKQylWZldUOBvUr0Gpu_bWr1yzSfSeYqbvXoKgcl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Had a great time at Amsterdam Dungeons! The whole experience was fun, interactive, and really well put together. I got picked to play the witch at the end and was chosen for another scene too, which made it even more memorable. The actors were brilliant, and the price felt fair for what you get. Definitely recommend it if you\'re in Amsterdam!','2025-07-22 18:27:56','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:59'),(12,3,'Kieran','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112724221494686846483/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVi7KvfSTcVIBzEdiFzaBm-pyd0JWjw1DOTGma1cUXPRLvplBTv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'A really fun experience, all the live actors were fantastic and fitted there roles well. Really good value for the price would definitely recommend a visit. My only complaint would be it did feel the group was too big and not enough sits for a few of the acts felt cramped in places.','2025-11-15 12:09:44','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:59'),(13,3,'Faith Rohani','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112627499636428343452/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXZfDZjyXy3o-qf7ufvTtO-MNPwy1Cg47Mja3pleMAuBpJ4P5JUA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Information before the fun stuff, the address given takes you to a door that then tells you to go around the building a bit more and yes. For us, we got sent to a random bar, and then we had to refind the address and use that lol.\n\nNo photos allowed during the tour, but it was good, you get truly engulfed into the stories.\n\nOh this was nice, informational, fun, interactive, funny and scary (if you get spooked easily) they pick people within the small groups to have you act out stuff, and there\'s signs and such for the chosen ones to do to make the storyline better. The actors were amazing, the group i had within it was fun, and i was chosen by my cousin as a woman who was accused to witchcraft, and needed to be burned at the stake. There were signs and such to tell me to scream and act like i was being burned alive to make the story more alive. Afterwards, i got a little fun paper, and the actor told me i did amazing and to go ahead and rejoin the group. Anywayz overall, great experience.','2025-06-24 20:53:08','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:59'),(14,3,'Nirvesh Seedeehul','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106178666719705793035/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUog_b2hrZ4CIrodXgEquC_SqQtutrBl-0yFX0GsmI7MU69uiX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Amazing experience. You can tell the actors r very passionate about what they\'re doing and overall the experience was really fun. My fav part has to be at the last story, won\'t spoil but the way it was, was so realistic you\'d think u were actually in a horror movie','2025-10-01 05:41:30','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:59'),(15,3,'Eman AlGhamdi','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105137132636310809354/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhfVoTC59PFUSCVOGrsGwis4BtQLEE7tM9ua40xawxCvIzQQ7K=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We had such an amazing time at Dungeon Amsterdam! The whole experience was a perfect mix of scary, funny, and surprising. We got genuinely spooked at times, laughed a ton, and were totally amazed by the actors and the atmosphere. The storytelling, sets, and jump scares were all so well done. Highly recommend if you’re looking for something fun and different to do in Amsterdam!','2025-11-22 07:34:04','Google','2025-12-11 10:33:59'),(16,4,'Aisha Patel','https://plus.google.com/112345678901234567890','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu34FGhi_87yh69749bkj8y1n2gC4zL2o1p',5,'Absolutely loved exploring the Old Town! The architecture is stunning, and there\'s so much history packed into every corner. The Edinburgh Castle views from the Royal Mile are breathtaking.','2025-12-04 16:04:26','Gemini','2025-12-11 10:34:26'),(17,4,'Jean-Pierre Dubois','https://maps.google.com/cid=1234567890987654321','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALm5wu21l23k4j4h3j56l7k8j910mn2o1pQ',4,'The Old Town is beautiful but can be very crowded, especially during peak season. We enjoyed wandering the side streets and finding hidden pubs. Worth the visit, but be prepared for the tourist hordes!','2025-11-27 16:04:26','Gemini','2025-12-11 10:34:26'),(18,4,'Kenji Tanaka','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109876543210987654321','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxCzX9sV_bQ1F2g6H4j5k7Ll8mN3oP2r4q',5,'A fascinating place. I took a walking tour which really brought the history of the area to life. Highly recommend a visit to St. Giles\' Cathedral while you are there.','2025-12-08 16:04:26','Gemini','2025-12-11 10:34:26'),(19,4,'Maria Rodriguez','https://search.google.com/local/writereview?placeid=ChIJeR-OqF1jV1QRLK73x4pWw9U','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ALm5wu0m1n2b3v4c5x6z7y8a9b0cd2e3f4g5h6i',4,'Loved the atmosphere in the Old Town. There are so many cute shops and restaurants. A little pricey in some areas but worth it for the experience.','2025-11-11 16:04:26','Gemini','2025-12-11 10:34:26'),(20,4,'David O\'Connell','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/119876543210987654321','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxBOz7wYkM_lXq-2qP4z