5','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:33'),(24,5,'Ftse','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118359534622794219504/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJcKUl53KJMUuKrHXHnp11lULsFvZ-uhpEk8ru35IsYej6ew=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This was definitely worth a visit. Yes, it does cost to go in but the handset made it worthwhile as they had an interactive app that helped the kids to learn, search and play. Out of all the historic sites we went to, they learnt the most at this site. The palace was beautiful and well maintained. There was one area (tight staircase heading to Mary\'s room) that would be an issue to get to for those who struggle to walk upstairs. There was no signage to provide another route. Other than that, we had a fabulous time and my 3 kids aged from 7 to 14 all enjoyed it.\n\nAll in all, a breathtaking','2025-10-29 09:55:23','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:33'),(25,5,'Christopher Notya','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110917857696601528878/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLusl4IJct9K0KUArazfxcULxZTUezyu_E0l13zUfmweUG4sg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Really cool place to visit! You get to walk through real royal rooms and learn lots of interesting stories (the audio guide is super helpful). The palace feels grand but still very peaceful, and the gardens are beautiful too. A perfect stop if you want a mix of history and chill vibes in Edinburgh.','2025-11-14 09:29:57','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:33'),(26,6,'Lianne Brouwer','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102388106487172163178/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIBAq2rDT3oe17Mlk08VDuWvLz6WohtZKA0-le7eGUrfKB4mQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'Great tour! It was very interesting and impressive to hear about the history of the close, and to walk through the actual remains. Our guide Sam was absolutely amazing. He was a great storyteller. Charismatic, and incredibly engaging.\nIf you\'re in Edinburgh, don\'t skip this tour, it is 100% worth it!','2025-11-13 22:15:33','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:46'),(27,6,'Ido Michel','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110382316013977176643/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2y6_3BrVj0QHsdKDsa2748dHhPisgGrFWuv5i1sWadwX4Ld4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Very interesting visit. Great insight on the past in Edinburgh.\nIt is a guided tour. Our guide was Lorraine and she did a great.\nThe tour is one hour tour. I went with my son almost 13 years old and it was not too scary.\nDefinitely, a must visit in Edinburgh.','2025-10-10 18:13:50','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:46'),(28,6,'Karmen','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100549348478228671601/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3j1GkarboeoWjR6_fm-jsVPvdmsQ1EdwOHufijIERLDb0IA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Great tour! Loved that the guide dresses up as someone from the time period and stays in character too. Our guide Daisy was so charismatic and passionate. Her enunciation was a 10/10 too. If you\'re thinking of buying the plague doctor mask keychain at the gift shop, note that it doesn’t actually come with the key ring, you only get the charm itself!','2025-10-13 16:00:43','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:46'),(29,6,'Brooke Hunter','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101531789665384640586/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuw4pZkU4GmVNlNUJMCFHfXu7f_DPRcyxrLX6sZlmAL7OK5w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'My second time doing The Real Mary Kings Close tour and I loved it even more this time. Such a highlight this tour, one of the best things to do in Edinburgh. Our tour guide\nAnthony was brilliant, he made the tour. I will be back for another tour when I come back to Edinburgh I love this place so much.','2025-10-21 20:07:15','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:46'),(30,6,'Karina Wall','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117779608029221356859/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItBdQYH9EyTvmExv9aETQ8YgfYPrNAQPUjCA36urrIICpQrQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'We pre-booked this tour ahead of our short trip to Edinburgh, and we are so glad we did.\nVery easy to find and very fascinating to find out about the Close and seeing the underground world of the city.\nOur tour guide, Sam Wise, was very knowledgeable and explained the history along with being entertaining too.\nIf your visiting Edinburgh , this is a must!','2025-11-23 07:37:43','Google','2025-12-11 10:34:46'),(31,7,'Timothy Cheung','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101189268452984469478/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG5_OQvDzg1mMMtzIQzZZLeUbBkIEWdltAkHVM1aC4jJmBc98uIA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'The Mob Museum absolutely exceeded our expectations! Every exhibit was incredibly well thought out — informative, immersive, and engaging from start to finish. You can tell a lot of care went into curating the history on both sides of organized crime and law enforcement rather than glamorizing it, which made the experience feel powerful and authentic.\n\nOne of the highlights for me was the educational section about law enforcement use of force. It tackled a serious topic in a respectful and factual way, giving insight into how split-second decisions are made in real situations. The scenario simulator was intense (in a good way!) and gave a whole new appreciation for how challenging that profession really is.\n\nWe walked out feeling entertained, educated, and impressed. You don’t just look at history here — you experience it. If you’re in Vegas and want something meaningful and memorable beyond the casinos, The Mob Museum is a must-see. I’d absolutely go again!','2025-12-02 17:33:22','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:00'),(32,7,'Nataku','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101420810389294015497/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTzskMbQB0w89T5WGeHN_9JfdRAFGi_NN5gAmVz5ws_WZLnRQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'I actually spent three hours here and I’m surprised that I spent so long in here because I didn’t expect this place to be so interesting. They had this mobster guy talking for 45 minutes. He also had the tasting downstairs of whiskey and it was good because they actually explained everything about the whiskey although I found it too long. That was also very informative as well. You have a cool speak easy downstairs make sure to go behind the painting because there’s a secret room there. make sure you check online for coupons. I got a 20% off coupon online.','2025-11-11 02:51:44','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:00'),(33,7,'J Joyner','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105547909881988222546/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyatthlOLo_P9RD0neyAOBgEAUxwBmnSZY-BR_x3LgTSLBQQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Loved this attraction. Was busier than I anticipated.  Go in the late afternoon...if you want to actually view the exhibits. Vegas is NOT dead! Interesting exhibits. We purchased the additional attractions for the distillery tasting and Interactive shooting scenario. My advice with live scenario, shoot first ask questions later!!  The distillery was great experience. Purchased a few travel sized bottles!!','2025-10-27 22:04:08','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:00'),(34,7,'Marika Lyons','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117568287176430613897/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlFDefrVmhEBdxa2lsaJ9moyUlAfj5PzPGTI1dbP2YiHEf0EU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'I picked two museums to go to while in Vegas for three days. The Mob Museum was one of them so fun! You can spend 3 hours or more in here. I will be back when I am in town. I want to check out The Underground Speakeasy and Distillery speakeasy. It was so cool down there. My niece and I did one interactive experience Firearm Training Stimulator. Wow! What a great experience we had. The gift shop is a must even if you\'re just looking. I did buy a T-shirt.','2025-11-15 02:25:00','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:00'),(35,7,'Daniel Trevino','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105170786480935269358/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/