he upgrades done to the museum recently are great! Low crowds, well priced tickets, and extensive exhibits. The volunteers are also very informative, especially in the dinosaur exhibit. I’m glad to see it’s been kept in amazing shape all these years.\n\nI enjoy coming back here frequently, even as an adult with no children. Thank you, Las Vegas Natural History museum, for great memories!','2025-10-07 20:31:51','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:13'),(39,8,'Sarah Foster','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100960361204477230004/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWicYBGQsOEyCBxwasZZcD-Y_cjcqMOHh_kZoiqTWPubBbIee4evw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Although I do have young children, I am on a trip without them this week and wanted something to do in Vegas that wasn\'t a casino. I came across a discounted ticket for the natural history museum through a third party site for $9 and decided to go.\n\nAs a solo adult it took me about an hour to walk through all the exhibits. I imagine if I would have had my children with me, it would have been closer to 3 hours.\n\nI found each exhibit interesting, but especially enjoyed the replica of King Tut\'s tomb.\n\nThe museum staff were all very nice and it was also super cool to meet an archeologist in the lab downstairs working on fossils. Overall I\'d highly recommend coming here, with or without children :)','2025-03-11 18:16:01','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:13'),(40,8,'Carter “Grandpa” Skillman','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103142571587074766448/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqK8ueFrdjLJt-BtmeARpHmC3L-TpNNCAys4ppyvfKzHi5wvb-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Grandparents put this place on your to-do list with your grandchildren! It has a lot of information for children. It\'s also easy on the senses!❤️💯','2025-06-19 22:59:21','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:13'),(41,9,'Anaïs Goupy','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116889931464333988022/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-Uj