O3zhdPq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Absolutely wonderful Zoo and Aquarium not far from the heart of Madrid.  Compared to Zoos in the US, this one is superb and very well kept & thoughtfully designed.  We loved it and, as a family that is very well traveled, I am surprised this Zoo is not higher rated in Google by other visitors.  All that said, our family of four loved it and I highly recommend it for a day of family fun.  Do buy your ticket online ahead of arriving - will save you some money.  We spent around 4 hours at the Zoo and purchased the basic entry which provided for plenty.  Enjoy!','2025-07-13 06:33:42','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:39'),(49,10,'Rasha Esp','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102329069836143121063/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIyCa2tDIBaF2omX2dukLeuFJZ1mdWKLvBTDmH85L_jlF6P4w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',3,'This is a really good Zoo but unfortunately most of the animals were having a nap! It’s like we payed for nothing, I mean if it’s gonna be like that why not make the price less expensive? I went there with my family excited to see tigers, lions, raccoons.. etc but none of them were awake. Maybe it’s due to the heat in Spain but I’m sure it’s hotter in their native habitat.\n\nJust don’t expect to see all animals.','2025-09-28 08:01:49','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:39'),(50,10,'Wakawaka Madrid','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116422520320093663061/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6JaBWIWLdswDAU5N6whw6ceq2iInZU7TKg0_N6g3wEL9Hot8rbA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'A perfect outing for families! This is a charming aquarium that, despite its compact size, is packed with fascinating exhibits. What makes it special for kids are the fun, interactive games and displays throughout which do a great job of keeping them engaged. We spent ages watching the playful penguins and the impressive sharks. Just remember to turn off your camera flash before you go in. Highly recommended for a fun and educational afternoon','2025-08-28 09:22:32','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:39'),(51,11,'Nicole Syriotis','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109139464342818201542/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_6l8Eo53S-Is-9JGriWi2wkpg5zHoh3xdPMfdMP6d9nJpx7Uz=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Eureka Skydeck – Incredible Views of Melbourne!\n\nA fantastic experience and definitely one of the best viewpoints in Melbourne. The 360° views are stunning — you can see the entire city, the coastline, and all the way out to the mountains on a clear day.\n\nThe space is well-organised, staff are friendly, and everything feels safe and smooth. The Edge Experience adds a fun little thrill if you like something extra!\n\nGreat for families, couples, or anyone visiting Melbourne. Highly recommend going around sunset for those magic colours over the skyline. 🌇✨','2025-11-24 16:26:20','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:53'),(52,11,'Dejan Gicevski','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108874439418373466301/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGB6HcQqHI3qgtC-prokSObNC3L_iL64fVPAotLJqJq_vyEEg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'A truly unique experience with absolutely stunning views from above. The 88th floor offers breathtaking panoramas of Melbourne, showcasing the city in all its beauty. Enjoying a drink or two at the bar makes the moment even more memorable.','2025-12-06 20:27:57','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:53'),(53,11,'Salman Momin','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111476962884677369163/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVf515fo23nqmmT-aTtEbDTS8pEJ8w2sW77ZJJcFTHrGVnu489-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'Our visit to Melbourne Skydeck was a truly memorable experience. It’s one of the best spots in the city to enjoy a panoramic view of Melbourne from high above. The observation deck gives a 360-degree view, allowing you to take in the skyline, river, and iconic landmarks all at once. Watching the sunset from the top was magical — the colors in the sky changed beautifully, making it perfect for photos. Many people also recommend the sunrise view for a peaceful start to the day.\n\nThe place is very family-friendly, and our kids were excited to spot famous buildings and watch the trams below. The interactive displays made the experience more fun for them. We tried some food and drinks from the café; although the prices were a bit expensive, we really enjoyed the mocktails, which were refreshing and tasty.\n\nIf you’re visiting Melbourne, this is a must-see attraction — especially for first-time visitors who want to see the city from above. A short visit can give you a great glimpse of the entire city. Overall, it’s a wonderful experience for both kids and adults.','2025-10-13 02:16:38','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:53'),(54,11,'Jigme Tenzin','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111344992761724152270/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiwenchrtE2uDym8ETdjky1Fg-N58gZ_Y6jvHmq4OeZR745AEm=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Melbourne Skydeck was a great experience with amazing panoramic views of the city in the afternoon. The staff were friendly and the whole visit was smooth and enjoyable. Having Wilson Parking right at the base is really convenient. Definitely a must visit when you’re in Melbourne.','2025-12-03 04:32:00','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:53'),(55,11,'Angela Padilla','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117816843073294187700/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1y3VC0yk8ZWl3TQ3nYUEgTRYd7K_gpKHV6hwo0_J90jokyYHpLg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'My 1st stop in Melbourne was here! I mean there is no other place with these views. Definitely a must for sunset, or just night views. You can get drinks and snacks too.','2025-11-24 08:26:39','Google','2025-12-11 10:35:53'),(56,12,'Jolie Foxx','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101240383770706854952/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpawYQBJJujcnISpEiZg2AaorqtngmzoxjJ-FLLMspeIUq8Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We\'ve been members here for years and totally love it. They\'ve renovated, especially with a cool new section where you can check out native marine life like biscuit starfish and spider crabs, and explore the rocky shore. The interactive rockpool is awesome for all ages, and their staff are super helpful, explaining all the species. One young Asian guy, I didn\'t catch his name, was amazing – he\'d notice us looking at something and then drop extra facts. My toddler was hooked and learned so much from him! We went on a Friday around lunchtime.\n\nThis place always delivers with spot talks all day long. We ended up staying over four hours. If you\'re coming from far, they have designated parking for a discount, but definitely check their website first. This time, we parked across at Crown Multi Parking and only paid $15 since we arrived before lunch and left around 4 pm.\nTheir membership is worth buying especially if you have a little and wants to come for few hours. I highly recommend.','2025-11-07 20:27:25','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:06'),(57,12,'Mr Smith','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104767833130021152675/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzDZCdnsQPfW7qRc14iZr1cNeizhbJg2OWHACD31CaSgg0PiloZQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',3,'It was ok, maybe were just spoilt other similar places around the word are way better.  I really wanted to give it 3.5 but that wastnt an option.  I went with my 15 year old daughter and we went as slow as we could and were in and out in under 2 hours. The exhibits were pretty good but there was a lot a areas with nothing. You also couldn\'t really do multiple laps more like a one way system.  It was also very tired and in need of a huge update.  So areas were unique and very enjoyable like jelly fish section.  The crocodile pen was closed which we were unaware of.  I does get really busy, I don\'t think it\'s worth queueing up for long unless you\'ve neve been to an aquarium before. It\'s also on the expensive side for what there is. Perth Aqua which I think is better is about $20 cheaper. The only good thing is kids age is 15 which is very fair.','2025-11-04 04:05:30','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:06'),(58,12,'H G','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107153352770962561257/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCprlOd8vb6i0U7ACIhTcNJAI5BRuYgPO2hkhYCyGNkZyn02E3Hw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Everything was so beautiful. Grateful to see the touch tank is mostly shells and one or two star fish. This is more fair on the wildlife.\nThey had so many jellyfish! My favourites! I was basically bouncing off the walls when I saw dwarf lions manes.\nIt wasn\'t too crowded when I went but I can see it being quite squishy when it is crowded but maybe they limit the number of people at a time? Hopefully','2025-11-27 06:28:47','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:06'),(59,12,'Alana Delaforce','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102703058010685734144/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzZmMgbrTMjQiKLDj8SqYDdZMHZ0o47ePhIbi1gsCxzx5NfXH0qg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'A visit to Sealife is a wortwhile and enjoyable activity for the whole family. There is something for everyone and a wide selection of exhibits. They have sharks, rays, turtles, jellyfish, seahorses a touch tank, frogs, snakes and penguins! The lift upgrade was happening during our visit so had to park the pram out front. We had reserved a pram spot but were strongly advise against it unless we absolutely needed it. Managed ok without it. They have \"free\" pictures which they ask you to pay $40 for at the end. To be fair they come in a very cute book and it is a neat souvenier. Overall, recommend. Will be good once the lift is fixed.','2025-10-26 10:35:06','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:06'),(60,12,'nickmontaldo','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104262332535957336620/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwd-Cvjqom-zakDK6Wlk9MIo9O-Bye9tI0TaJA6sm-HH6qZ0E=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',3,'Was a nice experience. takes around 2 hours to go through the whole aquarium. My criticism of it from when I went to this aquarium when it first opened and then 5 years ago is that they have way less marine life now. Not sure of it’s a cost cutting measure or for animal welfare? Some of the tanks looked amazing and some had 3 fish in them for example. And lots of walking around with big open spaces but would prefer more tanks of marine life.','2025-11-23 10:33:38','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:06'),(61,13,'Mr Smith','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104767833130021152675/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzDZCdnsQPfW7qRc14iZr1cNeizhbJg2OWHACD31CaSgg0PiloZQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',3,'A bit like sealife we were underwhelmed. Im not sure Melbourne Zoo lives up to its expectations of a world class Zoo. It had so much potential. Now we are spoilt!! San Diego Zoo for example, and even Singapore. Personally I preferred Perth Zoo.  I think the big thing for us was what appeared to be the lack of animals. Yes I know they could be sleeping but it felt like there was mostly only one of everything and you had buckleys chance seeing it. Funny enough you actually go to a zoo to see animals. Some of the enclosures felt small and not really good enough.  There were also no shows like most other zoos, normally a daily programme.  Also a lot of sections were closed either for a private function (not acceptable) or i don\'t know what. As with every entertainment event Food and Beverages are always a rip off but the quality, variety and costs here were terrible, again compared to other zoos. To be totally honest for the cost it\'s not really worth it. Fantastic for tiny kids otherwise forget it.','2025-11-05 07:10:36','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:19'),(62,13,'B L','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102899194548707157979/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEIkzMXpe5XuEIYsz9VfpeH0bj4AFerOgpt5AfF58brxl6dEXv=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'Had a really great time at Melbourne Zoo, the weather was a little crazy so not all the animals were out but it was still okay. the meerkats are so adorable, they are definitely used to people. Few food places within the zoo out didn’t get the opportunity to eat at them. Found a couple of gift shops with a huge range of memorabilia. You get to walk inside a cage with lemurs in it which was really cool. zoo is open from 9am onwards. I suggest bringing an umbrella because the ones in the gift shop are $40. There is also a beautiful Japanese garden and a koi fish pond. Great function rooms.','2025-11-11 10:31:14','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:19'),(63,13,'Aimee Engel','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105873367036120178756/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLS-fNrwqQ2LNFlc2axRXISeaG-Ou1JWhUnAjjMyKriuAhQ5A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'A great day out for the whole family. So many gorgeous animals to see. Our family favourites are the lemurs, meerkats, butterflies, giraffes and penguins. The staff are always friendly and they are happy to share their knowledge of the animals. My kids love the main play area near the carousel. A fun place for them to run around or sit down to eat.','2025-09-25 12:39:24','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:19'),(64,13,'Nick','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112170240230415744558/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6zw-KQKhQuJvKnjCjvgHx5a_IENBBgK_Fm4xYxFnhRD0Ymdw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'We had a fantastic day out! The zoo was huge and had so many animals to see. The food was yummy and prices were super affordable. Only bummer was the butterfly garden was closed when we visited. Would definitely come back, there\'s just so much to see and enjoy!','2025-10-31 08:30:13','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:19'),(65,13,'Nadya Majeed','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117714247156861893246/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXImZa8tzoijlsvDn_JbZDfy6zp7Hw9LXhJJePTaKNFlXbfppr6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'we spent 3 hours here (skipped a handful of exhibits). great zoo to visit. super easy to navigate, great variety of animals. animals look well taken care of, with a lot of thought and effort put into their habitats and enrichment. lots of education for visitors. appreciate all the conservation efforts and information as well. loved this zoo and highly recommend it.','2025-09-23 10:16:42','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:19'),(66,14,'Clint Watson','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100093514463682171352/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVb50wwodo-j8xW58nF_JqZ8BmWi2H7JzqP_xLdK3B4CUgMxXP5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',4,'Luminosa at Jungle Island is nice, but definitely on the mediocre side. The lantern displays are colorful and make for good photos, but the whole experience is pretty quick — about a 30-minute walkthrough.\n\nParking is also pricey at $20, on top of the ticket cost, which feels steep for such a short visit. It’s worth seeing once if you’re already nearby, but I wouldn’t call it a must-do.\n\nOverall, a pleasant experience, just not quite worth the total cost.','2025-11-29 17:03:22','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:31'),(67,14,'Mar & Terry','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103798042474820186939/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqztKIF0p8Y_fj6WPgOSVUCielazMP3GxE43ljmeOL0bnWOFUP5A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Went for Luminosa last night and had a great time! The lights are gorgeous and our entire family had so much fun.\n\nWe love that they change it up every year so it\'s different each time you go and this year was beautiful!\n\nThey also have a great Christmas section this year with gorgeous Christmas trees and themed treats.\n\nParking is separate from your ticket entrance so keep that in mind','2025-11-17 23:29:46','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:31'),(68,14,'Adam Mighton','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114689037151875161354/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQZsSEODGRrSYDC0Upmx6-8fnEqnkGowZZYoPpY2UjPw5Ezwemhg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'Our family of 5 attended jungle Island while visiting Miami before a cruise. We enjoyed the animals that were on display that all looked to be in good health and content with their environment.\n\nThe decor was nice and would have been nice to have seen the light show and exhibitions at night.\n\nStaff were very interactive and friendly.\n\nWe especially enjoyed the capaberas, owls, and the various monkeys.\n\nParking being significantly extra was probably the biggest disappointment for us and would reduce the amount of times we would attend in the future.','2025-11-18 17:37:16','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:31'),(69,14,'Dmitriy Kozlov','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108876061162607522155/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXAJk-168R5xiRB_C5xiDUDljmL0GU6Xiu9sRztls_y0eAj9g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',4,'Everything in this park looks magnificent and beautiful, but I\'m really surprised that parking costs $20 at the entrance and you have to pay another $20 at the exit, otherwise the barrier won\'t open. And, of course, you have to buy tickets. $125 for us (one child and three adults) came out to $125. So be prepared to pay $40 for parking.','2025-11-26 03:21:20','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:31'),(70,14,'theBrownman28','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106680668049531695382/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWO9dIYUp3gEA0YlH3qvU0TBultz0VOkdllbDKjLtbWxs6kgVAUwA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'This place was awesome! Kind of like a small zoo but the REAL experience is the Lemur Experience. Getting to feed and hangout with the cute little Lemurs was an experience of a lifetime. Highly recommend if you\'re able to stop by.','2025-10-15 17:46:10','Google','2025-12-11 10:36:31'),(71,15,'Les Schwartz','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113691980279137507434/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHl9WilYn_lrfv-tPRptTvMXtwuKJ2J5O525UsF2CbKIywDA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',3,'Firstly, all that is advertised is true. But the experience is more perception. There is a tour but at night so there isn\'t much to see except alot of rich people\'s boats (yachts) and houses. In other words the haves (them) and the have not (you). And if it rained, with rain protectors, you\'ld see nothing. Yes, a tourist attraction (or trap). Carting 300 to 400 people in and out of a boat something like a herd. To get a supposed best seat an hour before the departure is absurd. There is no best seat. Total waste of time. The tour guide does his best to entertain and inform those who pay attention to whatever rich people data is worth learning. Then on to the private island of food and entertainment. The food is mediocre at best. Eat all you can (not all you can eat). Chicken fingers and ribs. All I hoped was to stay well afterwards. Dessert not included. Ice cream bar, there, but closed. Then the Hawaiian stage show. Uncomfortable seating. Ok show. Highlight, fire dance. Herded back to the boat and back to the dock. Value: I suppose so especially if you got discounted tickets on Groupon. Expensive drinks or board. They offer a parking discount worth taking advantage of. Overall certainly family friendly. Certainly for tourists. Certainly worth doing....once.','2025-11-28 18:48:05','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:01'),(72,15,'Clare Bear forever','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117623543873135368423/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGQOofttBqG2D6R-PN0AoVTzsb7-pm4o5Bgh62keECHXE4m2kwDw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'The ride was lovely. To get a small glimpse of how the other side lives looks beautiful. The all you can eat barbecue was good. The chicken strips were salty but the ribs were good. The after dinner show was great. The island where everything took place is beautiful. Of course all the staff were pleasant. Purchase tickets on Groupon.','2025-08-30 14:50:33','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:01'),(73,15,'Yuri Guerrero','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117080735773642698931/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfcrihXvuN-pa_3Pscj0jSWKNXjPlGO_TErhuarV6BV5Vz7eXGlg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'I had an incredible time on the Jungle Queen Riverboat tour! The views from the river were absolutely stunning, offering picturesque scenes of the waterways and surrounding nature that made every moment visually spectacular. The highlight was definitely the Polynesian dance performance at the island—vibrant, energetic, and so engaging. The staff were friendly and the atmosphere was lively, making it a memorable outing. The only downside was the food, which was just okay and could use some improvement, but it didn’t detract from the overall enjoyment. Highly recommend this tour for the amazing views and cultural entertainment!','2025-07-13 21:36:30','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:01'),(74,15,'Krysti Mikkonen','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112556638916994332769/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWv1gz2mwm2BZsw52jiLOBBtp_HUX2N0jDArfAuFvnHiyJF_U7pAA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2',5,'Despite the rain (at times pouring rain) we had a great experience. We had 13 people in our party and we had the upper deck to ourselves. Parker, our guide, was entertaining, informative, and funny. The big pack of iguanas sitting on the dock as we went out on the tour was an added bonus. As we were heading back in to dock at the end of the tour, right before disembarking, the rain started to really come down and the team gave us all disposable rain coats and offered to let us stay on the boat a bit until it let up.','2025-12-01 21:37:36','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:01'),(75,15,'Jamie Wemken','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113219985780618736940/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOmeGCaLc9QkMR9DCEtzvcWiooL0rbM9hbGUKqUj9tJ-f7brs6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',4,'Fun experience. Our guide was knowledgeable and amusing. It\'s best to arrive early if you want a good seat with a view. The drink prices were about what you would expect. The bbq dinner was average, the weight staff was friendly, and service was quick.\n\nCons: There was no air flow on the boat, so sitting on it for 30+ mins in the heat waiting for departure, surrounded by 100 people got hot and smelly. It would have been nice if they had fans to circulate the air. Cup holders on the seats would have been beneficial. Also, the bathroom stalls were very snug.\nOverall we had a great time and I would recommend the tour','2025-09-01 12:53:12','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:01'),(76,16,'Juliya Kurlyanchik','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100249555959764474224/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_ZOyJecrnLK7y-u0IQZ7miBLmQbrCwIkuw1XuQI04yRsG2RHyhg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Such an amazing experience! The installations were absolutely stunning — bright, detailed, and incredibly realistic. We loved it, even though the weather was a bit chilly and the drive took us about an hour each way.\n\nI highly recommend arriving at least three hours before closing, because two hours definitely weren’t enough for us. Everything is so vibrant and picturesque. A wonderful experience, even after the main safari area had already closed!','2025-11-29 05:39:24','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:15'),(77,16,'Sarah Westleigh-Soldano','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112254062978459170052/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUs9cuoJDNqiv_QdSi3-KR4VeYrMUcFNsXdjyHhI0WzD_o2rUCK=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'What an incredible safari tour! With so many animals to view it was well worth the admission cost. When driving through, you receive (at your wish) a voice guided tour that you can get scanning the qr code which provides you with facts and history of each animal within the park. What makes this park even more incredible, is you can walk through another park where you view birds, flamingos, giraffes and go on a boat tour (extra fee). There is a small amusement park along with gorgeous flowers and fascinating decorative paths to walk through. Definitely a place for those between 2-120 years!!!!','2025-11-01 01:16:50','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:15'),(78,16,'Ben L','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111578011996670969104/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAdBhi7uGYZho0qqotdxgkqdc36reszLUpgRgn0rGsqi1oTK-N=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'We love Lion Country Safari! It’s such an amazing place to bring the family and friends. You are allowed to respectfully drive through the park and take in the surreal sights of the diverse array of animals and habitats. You can take your time to truly appreciate everything that’s available. Once you’re done driving through the safari, you can spend some time at the park to continue to observe Gods creatures, grab a snack, let the kiddos play at the waterpark, or purchase some souvenirs. I highly recommend spending a day at the Safari.','2025-10-18 18:48:33','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:15'),(79,16,'Stephen Toth','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115004728078584979927/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwm0P79f2oAfq9BqQdDHTYRw2qpcJNWx1QD5VDz7IZNwx_6btR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',4,'There\'s a nice variety of animals to look at during the visit with an informative audio guide that\'s pleasant to listen to while you drive through the safari.  Don\'t expect the animals to \"perform\" for you. This is a natural environment very similar to their own. Most of what you see is grazing, though you might get some interaction. But that\'s the point of a preserve, to see the animals as undisturbed as possible. Very well suited for children with fun stuff to do after the tour.','2025-12-02 12:18:28','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:15'),(80,16,'kevin velasquez','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117346150682939356771/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbWxVOcqTB9lNHg3FPjOY3F-XyiplAGp7hLNcn1NWjv6kHO0M=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'It was a nice visit! Although I would like to have had the windows down the animals didn’t seem interested in approaching our vehicles but we had our windows up, it was nice to drive through once and walk around we did the feeding and petting area we enjoyed the boat tour and the maze. We didn’t eat there but we stopped by a Mexican restaurant close by avanges or something like that. But it was a nice time we left there happy. Wasn’t too hot walking around we ran through splash pad but didn’t stay there’s','2025-10-19 12:12:49','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:15'),(81,17,'Holly P','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104539674559380055507/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy6scwe-KTZzx0_0-yUKtuiZZj-JkKIfDoCcatywj3AeMHXL_aRg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'The catacombs of Paris are great for history buffs, people who love architecture, people who love morbid or creepy stuff, people who are are spiritual or religious, and anyone interested in learning about the truth behind Paris history. Definitely worth the trip to see, it’s amazing to see how such a dense city grapples with the limited space and demands of a large population. Absolutely reminds you of how human you are. Definitely worth booking a private tour. Audioguides are only €6 and you can reserve on site, but I booked a tour guide. Awesome trip. Loved seeing the altar and Christian artworks and crosses. May all of the souls in the Catacombs rest in peace.','2025-10-30 20:26:54','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:41'),(82,17,'Jamie Higgs-Dey','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115763750949592100729/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRMXceQCm8O28O98PGW5cI7QOPsvq_farl_08KcK06VWOMOZd5=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'The labyrinth of limestone is fascinating, everyone buried together without hierarchy is humbling and to walk through and experience this is very unique. A must do when you’re in Paris. The process of finding and creating the catacombs is also incredible.\nGreat self-guided tour, the audio guide is detailed enough to give you plenty of info without being boring or too lengthy.\nThe queue system for the different time slots works well. Staff were helpful.\nI would highly recommend this, it’s not too far away from the centre, if you like walking you could walk there or just take a quick ride on the metro. We booked tickets in advance and they were rather limited as it’s so popular.','2025-11-09 14:27:59','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:41'),(83,17,'B S','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118374009318834529273/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwiaItsu881S69bJVzZOknPUjGBtqPnso4MWqNAWIxwz0DPw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'Excellent place to visit, on the day of visting, I noticed at 11am all the tickets for the day were sold out for the Friday,  so it\'s worth getting a ticket in advance. It\'s organised well from the way the scheduled times are filtered to the quick security checks. The audio machines are high quality and easy to use, they are available in different languages. Security is tight and there are frequent visits by security within the catacombs as the greatest damage is actually done by people touching the bones.  There were over 6 million people\'s bones here and here there was no hierarchy so poor people could have been next to the rich. It is sad that this catacomb was discovered as houses caved in due to the underground void leading to the discovery. The tickets can be booked directly from the place and in this instance there is no need for a guide as the guide cannot jump the queue and its a one way system, full price with an audio guide is 31 euros, 25 euros for reduced price, and 12 for people aged 5 to 17 years, it is expensive in comparison to other sites like the Eiffel Tower or the Lourve. Note the catacombs will shut from 03 Nov 2025 to spring 2026. Tickets can be booked 7 days in advance.\nThe visitor entrance is located at the following address:\n1, Avenue du Colonel Henri Rol-Tanguy (place Denfert-Rochereau)\n75014 Paris. There is a limit on the size of bag that can be taken (40×30cm), no strollers tripods etc are allowed. Flash photography is allowed so long as it doesn\'t cause issues to other  guests. The place is limited to 200 per day and it is not encouraged to visit if you have mobility issues, there are 131 steps going down and 112 to ascend, some places are slippery so care must be taken, the walk is 1.5km and can take an hour to negotiate.','2025-10-17 05:57:29','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:41'),(84,17,'Ariel Jewel','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111418563977977305187/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUJ20t0qJGLqLr2ghrJAuGNAubPfRtHyQozXLFo3nbAVdJl5A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'as someone who loves horror (hello as above so below) I adored the catacombs. it’s located in a random little square in the middle of the streets, and upon entering you climb down 10m of stairs, where the vistable portion of the catacombs starts and is laid out like a museum. I loved this format, it made the visit so much more immersive. note that floors can be slippery though.\n\nIn each area of the catacombs there’s a free audio guide piece and an information board on the history of the catacombs, and also certain engravings on the walls that are highlighted including dates and words from more than a hundred years ago. I also liked that the place wasn’t absolutely teeming with people and that there were still areas where you could be alone with the ambiance.\n\nhonestly walking silently, 20m below ground, through the mountains of bones and remains is so cool and unique and memorable?? there was also a guide there who was absolutely stellar at her work, and who provided detailed information of the catacombs and current restoration works.\n\nmy dumb ahh also bumped straight into a skull and promptly gave myself a heart attack so there’s THAT\n\ngift shop is also super fun!','2025-11-24 20:10:35','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:41'),(85,17,'Penny Gaffney','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100865124178850645279/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWb80s2guqAoj8ime63oMCAX6_Lzk1OrW6MONXDsebhyFJJo377iQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8',5,'One of those fascination all human has with dead thing and to see it in such a volume is fascinating!\nI visited the Catacombs of Paris in my first time to Paris in 2018 and this place was the most standout from that time so when I had a chance to come back to Paris again this was the only place I wanted to revisit. (And the cheese fondue restaurant)\nI think they might have lower a cap number of people in each time slot now since when I tried to book tickets most of the time slots are all sold out and only a couple left for the 2 days I was in Paris.\nIt was also very quiet and not many people down there. It was super nice to be able to take your time to walked around and look at things slowly! I really enjoyed that 💀\nI didn\'t see the skull coin souvenir last time so I was so glad to get some magnet and coin this time! 🪙☠️\nThe staff was very friendly and professional! Great gift shop at the finish of the tunnel!\nSomehow I blocked out information about the 300 spirel stairs to go down into the tunnel and come back up from last time, got a bit dizzy 🥴 going down too fast 😂\nDefinitely a recommendation of thing to do in Paris.','2025-11-16 10:32:05','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:41'),(86,18,'Geoffrey Caron-Lormier','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104896848385424420159/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQkYBP6vEbySF0YmByac8sifoKEBUZokIh7j91X-46kWP6PSyXLg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'A good experience. Small but well populated with a good range of animals, including a manatee which we had not seen before.\n\nWe spent 4h30 on site, including a quick lunch and the little shop at the end.\n\nThe enclosures looked big enough for the animals.\n\nOverall, we enjoyed and likely to go back at some point, reminded us of the London Zoo.','2025-10-31 16:03:17','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:55'),(87,18,'Rana O.','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114020945902660374977/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLRN7-Y-mwJTwBgfQvtuTGvjIBi8X7Pm6dyCLEFgdi7IHc48rw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6',5,'We have spent 3 hours exploring the zoo. We enjoyed our time. The zoo route is clear and guides u easily between animals. It contains a good variety of animals & birds. It could have been great if there were an elephant and bear.\nA recommendation for sure!','2025-07-22 08:39:17','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:55'),(88,18,'Laura Grieve','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107397444383511756787/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLRpLxr-0lKuFsHSF_16krxK5l1LO6xXy1eJQ78c6w86KcOGg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'Brillant zoo. Lovely  enclosures, staff were very helpful. All animals looked well maintained. Terrible weather and the zoo closed for safety and we were given a full refund. Didnt make the gift shop so my teddy collection is short 🤣 great morning out no crowds','2025-10-27 19:23:50','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:55'),(89,18,'Vincent M','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118365014739243027327/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9NuzuiayqcaXweoG9kQsTF_y5DilaY2eLls1vateFWu132wb7=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4',5,'An amazing Zoo, with many animals and a lot to explore. My favorite points were:\nThe big bird aviary where the birds can fly over, next you.\nThe tropical greenhouse\nThe savannah area where only a water feature and an electric fence seems to separate visitors from the animals.','2025-11-11 12:32:27','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:55'),(90,18,'Maddie D','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113095243651841836803/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL640PbAACXMrjO5goOvy2Z_v5trvzWwEyRt--oX2OVrfQB1A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'Easily one of the best zoos I have been to. Went on a day where it was rainy midday and the zoo was nearly empty. We had great weather and the animals were awake and active. The enclosures seemed like they had planets of space for the animals within them and the animals seemed content, which made me happy.','2025-07-25 15:14:04','Google','2025-12-11 10:37:55'),(91,19,'Dr Robert Nash','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102993876013775611461/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhD4_YBsV-D0HlPJ8OqvCLqdP4DvYzCeN7s1uynS6RhAEObLVj1A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo',5,'A very old, interesting, and wonderful cemetery.\nWalking through the cemetery gives you a tour of both history and art.  I highly recommend it.  It would be easy to spend an afternoon here.','2025-12-05 17:54:47','Google','2025-12-11 10:38:12'),(92,19,'julie demdam','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103348019379082804349/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU91YZc2gBzRVDSGV7oB8mrrta5ct-x15qsWBAMAeFWemgfia7e=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'Of my 5 visits to Paris, I’ve been here 3 times. This most current visit was the quickest as it started to rain as soon as we entered.\n\nOur biggest mistake was not taking a photo of the map as soon as we entered. We ended up bumping into a couple of Americans with a map so we ended up getting a snap of theirs.\nWe didn’t really have a solid plan. All I knew was that I wanted to see Jimmy and that’s it. We ended up on quite the adventure finding Jimmy. It seemed like we walked in circles.\nThe great thing about this cemetery is that there are so many famous people interred here. And many notable families. With that said, you’ll see some elaborate tombstones.\nYou do see a few employees walking the grounds. They all walk around during closing time, ringing their bells to let you know they’re about to close so you better skidaddle or you’ll be locked in.\nI’m going to do a walking tour the next time I’m in town so I can cover more ground. I’m always so overwhelmed when I’m there\nIt is however super sad to see the graves that are clearly unattended, sometimes looking like they’ve been abandoned.','2025-10-20 00:19:28','Google','2025-12-11 10:38:12'),(93,19,'Carl Fulghieri','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108288912145836256119/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrphoBf7rDhcRYpJJrTGsp7Dgqorzq01Qfq7_ZElD_T2MUuwB4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3',5,'A good site to visit in Paris. There are many interred here who have influenced and inspired you — even if you don’t know it yet. During peak tourist season there are a number of friendly attendants to provide maps and directions. Toilets are in the south. Some accessibility concerns: many ways are cobbled and some steep, although there is a slope going around the whole cemetery.','2025-10-09 20:50:40','Google','2025-12-11 10:38:12'),(94,19,'Trouvaille B','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103591100681277977228/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhxHckC3MHsxSXPM93V-J07afnLSJ3TCkK6F63-F5UXEAGYpf7UQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5',5,'This cemetery was so great, I ended up going twice. Some of the headstones are so amazing, you have to just walk around and see where you end up. If I could have spent a day here, I would have.\n\nI do understand that headstones are close together and probably difficult to maintain, but in some areas, the weeds are so tall and areas are overgrown :(','2025-09-19 19:08:18','Google','2025-12-11 10:38:12'),(95,19,'Martin K.','https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102818011791033311662/reviews','https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWC8OpmDugjj4N_OXg4CVEY-9yXg7SzSEgeX4StoBbljHtKPWCt=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7',5,'The counterpoint to the glittering Parisian boulevards.\nDefinitely worth a visit at any time of year, but especially outside the summer months. The gloomier the weather, the more beautiful it becomes. Creates a sense of closeness to people you have never known.\nEvery grave tells its own story of transience, sorrow, but also creativity and inspiration.\nTake your time, you can easily spend a couple of hours here.\nIt\'s best to give the Morrison tomb a wide berth, as any sense of reflection tends to be drowned out there.','2025-10-05 14:08:16','Google','2025-12-11 10:38:12');
